Document: NoiseTexture2D
Path: godot/classes/class_noisetexture2d.rst
Summary: Describes the NoiseTexture2D class, which uses noise generators to fill texture data and can generate normal maps, utilizing threads for generation.
Inherits: Texture2D < Texture < Resource < RefCounted
Description:
Uses the FastNoiseLite library or other noise generators to fill the texture data of your desired size. NoiseTexture2D can also generate normal map textures.

The class uses Threads's to generate the texture data internally, so Texture2D.get_image() may return null if the generation process has not completed yet. In that case, you need to wait for the texture to be generated before accessing the image and the generated byte data:

GDScript:
    var texture = NoiseTexture2D.new()
    texture.noise = FastNoiseLite.new()
    await texture.changed
    var image = texture.get_image()
    var data = image.get_data()
---CHUNK---
Document: NoiseTexture2D
Path: godot/classes/class_noisetexture2d.rst
Summary: Defines the properties available for configuring a NoiseTexture2D resource.

Properties
- as_normal_map (bool): If true, the generated noise is treated as a normal map. Default: false.
- bump_strength (float): The strength of the bump effect when the noise is used as a normal map. Default: 8.0.
- color_ramp (Gradient): A Gradient to remap the noise values to colors.
- generate_mipmaps (bool): If true, mipmaps are generated for the texture. Default: true.
- height (int): The height of the generated texture in pixels. Default: 512.
- in_3d_space (bool): If true, the noise is generated in 3D space, allowing for depth. Default: false.
- invert (bool): If true, the noise values are inverted. Default: false.
- noise (Noise): The Noise resource to use for generating the texture.
- normalize (bool): If true, the noise values are normalized to the range [0, 1]. Default: true.
- resource_local_to_scene (bool): If true, the resource will be duplicated for each scene instance. Default: false.
- seamless (bool): If true, the noise texture will tile seamlessly. Default: false.
- seamless_blend_skirt (float): Controls the blend skirt for seamless tiling. Default: 0.1.
- width (int): The width of the generated texture in pixels. Default: 512.
